title: Ask HN: First Time Director of Web Platform – Advice?
text:
I've been a software engineer for over seven years now, I quit my old job at the bank two weeks ago because I was doing project management + dev work for only dev pay. I applied to a small local company that is seeking a digital transformation. The owner liked me a lot, I'm set to start in a few days.

How can I make sure that I crush this? I'd like to stay with the company for a few years at least, and make a career pivot to being a director. Are there other certs I can take? I think the thing I have to remember the most is to display confidence. Are there directors out there with advice for younger people? I'm even thinking of cold calling/msging directors on linkedin to ask them for advice.

How would you go about it?

Ask HN: Kubernetes Worth It?
text: To paraphrase Phil Greenspan’s famous LISP quote: “Does any sufficiently complicated micro service architecture contain an ad hoc, informally specified, bug ridden, slow implementation of half of kubernetes?” Thought that might be an interesting way of saying is it worth bitting the bullet and spending the effort to understand and use kubernetes.
